manville corp on the verge of emerging from six years of 
bankruptcy court protection on sunday reported its net income 
increased 9 percent in the third quarter as sales of the companys 
fiber glass and forest products rose 
for the quarter ended sept 30 denverbased manville said net 
income totaled 535 million or 196 a share up from 486 
million or 176 a share a year ago 
net sales during the period rose 7 percent to 5843 million 
from 5479 million in the 1987 third quarter 
manville president and chief executive tom stephens noted the 
positive performance was achieved despite the continued 
competitiveness in most construction related markets 
sales of the companys fiber glass and forest products rose 7 
percent in the quarter 
manville filed for chapter 11 protection in 1982 while being 
deluged with asbestos injury and propertydamage lawsuits by 1986 
property damage claims alone had come to a staggering 85 billion 
or about 40 times the companys total assets the company also 
faced more than 17000 personal injury claims in the billions of 
dollars 
earlier this month the us supreme court rejected the last 
challenge to manvilles reorganization plan virtually assuring the 
companys emergence from protection from its creditors under 
chapter 11 of the bankruptcy code the plan calls for establishing 
certain trusts to settle claims of asbestos health victims 
with our strong operating performance and solid balance sheet 
were ready to exit chapter 11 and move forward stephens said 
for the first nine months net earnings were 1223 million or 
431 a share down 8 percent from 1326 million or 473 a share 
the current period includes certain charges and costs associated 
